  "body": "### Description\r\nWe are currently evaluating besu as mining backend client for our ethermine mining pool (second largest ethereum pool). Currently the eth_getWork response does not include the current block number as fourth return value. Currenty both geth & parity return the block number as last value. Access to the block number makes it easier to initialize the PoW validation engine.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n`curl --data '{\"method\":\"eth_getWork\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1,\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\"}' -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -X POST localhost:8545`\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** Return hex encoded current block number in eth_getWork response\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** Current block number is not included in the eth_getWork response\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: besu/v1.4.4/linux-x86_64/openjdk-java-11\r\n\r\n\r\n",
